{
  "texts": [
    "These essays were written as part of a performance assessment.",
    "Pupils in the seventh grade wrote a narrative with descriptive elements based on the ballad \"The Sorcerer's Apprentice\" (in German \"Der Zauberlehrling\") by J. W. Goethe.",
    "Those in the eighth grade wrote narratives inspired by two paintings by Edward Hopper (\"Nighthawks\" and \"Gas\").",
    "To ensure representativeness despite a small corpus, we selected narratives since they are taught in all German school types.",
    "Teacher Essay ScoringThe 20 student essays were presented to 𝑁 = 37 teachers with the task of reading the texts and assessing them according to 10 pre-defined criteria using a six-point Likert scale, ranging from Not true at all to Fully applies."
  ]
}